  <div class="s3-ingredients">
    <div class="s3-ingr">
      <div class="s3-ingr-num">☕</div>
      <div>
        <span class="s3-ingr-role">Drains fluid · Reduces puffiness</span>
        <span class="s3-ingr-name">Caffeine</span>
        <p class="s3-ingr-desc">A vasoconstrictor that narrows blood vessels and stimulates lymphatic drainage. When delivered into the dermis, it directly reduces the fluid pooling causing under-eye bags and constricts the micro-capillaries responsible for bluish discoloration. In creams, caffeine never gets deep enough to do this.</p>
        <span class="s3-ingr-target">→ Targets cause #3: fluid pooling & puffiness</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="s3-ingr">
      <div class="s3-ingr-num">💧</div>
      <div>
        <span class="s3-ingr-role">Plumps · Hydrates · Fills hollows</span>
        <span class="s3-ingr-name">Hyaluronic Acid</span>
        <p class="s3-ingr-desc">Holds up to 1,000x its weight in water, plumping and hydrating thinning under-eye tissue. Liftora's micro-needles are made of hyaluronic acid — meaning 100% of the needle itself dissolves into an additional HA dose directly in the dermis. You get the delivery mechanism AND the ingredient in one.</p>
        <span class="s3-ingr-target">→ Targets cause #2: thinning skin & hollowness</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="s3-ingr">
      <div class="s3-ingr-num">🍊</div>
      <div>
        <span class="s3-ingr-role">Brightens · Fights pigmentation</span>
        <span class="s3-ingr-name">Vitamin C</span>
        <p class="s3-ingr-desc">Inhibits melanin production and oxidizes hemoglobin that has leaked from broken capillaries — the exact mechanism behind the dark brownish-purple tint. Vitamin C molecules are too large to penetrate skin without mechanical assistance. Via Liftora's micro-channels, it reaches the pigmentation at its source.</p>
        <span class="s3-ingr-target">→ Targets cause #1: oxidized hemoglobin & dark tint</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="s3-ingr">
      <div class="s3-ingr-num">🔬</div>
      <div>
        <span class="s3-ingr-role">Rebuilds · Stimulates collagen</span>
        <span class="s3-ingr-name">Peptides (Matrixyl 3000)</span>
        <p class="s3-ingr-desc">Short chains of amino acids that signal skin cells to produce more collagen and elastin. Matrixyl 3000 has been shown in clinical studies to increase collagen synthesis by up to 350%. As the under-eye dermis thickens, blood vessels become less visible and skin regains its youthful opacity. Results build progressively over 4–6 weeks.</p>
        <span class="s3-ingr-target">→ Targets cause #2: long-term collagen rebuilding</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="s3-ingr">
      <div class="s3-ingr-num">🛡️</div>
      <div>
        <span class="s3-ingr-role">Protects · Locks in results</span>
        <span class="s3-ingr-name">Ceramides</span>
        <p class="s3-ingr-desc">Lipid molecules that form the protective barrier of the skin. The under-eye area produces almost no natural lipids and is chronically dehydrated. Ceramides seal the micro-channels after treatment, reinforce the skin barrier, and prevent the water loss that makes dark circles worse. Without ceramides, results from the other ingredients would fade much faster.</p>
        <span class="s3-ingr-target">→ Seals results and protects the barrier long-term</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

